<section id="background">

<h2>Background</h2>

<p>

My professional background is in hospitality, where I worked as a chef in fast-paced kitchens that demanded consistency, communication, precision, and continuous improvement. Although very different from research, the experience taught me how to build reliable processes, adapt quickly, and make sound decisions under pressure.

</p>

<p>

Over time my interests shifted toward writing, independent research, and understanding how structured methods influence attention, learning, and behaviour. Generative AI became a natural extension of that work—not because it replaces thinking, but because it makes it possible to explore, organise, and refine ideas more effectively.

</p>

<p>

Today I am looking for opportunities where I can contribute to research, technical writing, documentation, AI evaluation, workflow design, or knowledge management, while continuing to learn alongside people who are building the future of human–AI collaboration.

</p>

